column180:
18/Feb/19 10:37 AM;nekia;If you add "ssl-target-name-override" grpc option in your config.json, it should work.
{code:java}
      "orderers": {
        "orderer.example.com": {
          "tlsCACerts": {
            "path": "/tmp/crypto/ordererOrganizations/example.com/orderers/orderer.example.com/tls/ca.crt"
          },
          "url": "grpcs://orderer.example.com:7050",
          "grpcOptions": {
            "ssl-target-name-override": "orderer.example.com"
          }
        }
      },
{code}
But I'd like to remove this requirement (adding 'orderer' configuration to config.json ) for docker environment.
Root cause of this failure which is initially provided by this JIRA is that 'localhost:7050', not 'orderer.example.com:7050' is included in discover result in docker environment as a orderer url. I'll keep analyzing more.;;;

