CONFIG transactions have a different structure compared to regular endorser transactions.

As a result, in Explorer they are always missing the txhash (it is not being returned by the nodejs SDK, perhaps an upstream bug). Additionally, other fields such as rwsets are also not being synced correctly and the tx row in the database is mostly empty. rwsets could be synced already if the correct code was added in SyncService.js (see here: https://github.com/sigma67/hypersec/commit/87d388bbfedc642c1f72447bd2effae8fc684bd3). 

Inspecting in frontend with the transaction popup however is only possible after the txhash is returned by node SDK. 

The transaction from nodejs sdk looks like this currently:

{code:json}
{
  "payload": {
    "header": {
      "channel_header": {
        "type": 1,
        "version": 0,
        "timestamp": "2020-12-11T09:08:36.000Z",
        "channel_id": "mychannel",
        "tx_id": "",
        "epoch": {
          "low": 0,
          "high": 0,
          "unsigned": true
        },
        "extension": {
          "type": "Buffer",
          "data": []
        },
        "typeString": "CONFIG"
      },
      "signature_header": {
{code}

