column192:
27/Apr/19 1:54 AM;mnobilio;Given the [Node SDK sample|https://fabric-sdk-node.github.io/tutorial-mutual-tls.html], it appears the credential linkage between the client and the Fabric CA server is buried within the metadata of the client cert.
h3. *Therefore it appears the OU field specified during cert creation (such as "clientAppOne") is a critical value and  must match the ID registered with the Fabric CA server ("clientAppOne"), as well as the affiliation.   This is a critical linkage that is not documented.*


Note the *OU* field specified during cert creation: */OU=clientAppOne/OU=org1.department1*
