column173:
23/Jul/18 7:16 PM;Tecnalia;[~srinivas640] We had those problems too.

Temporally error is mostly times caused by a wrong DNS configuration that blocks container requests. This usually happens on corporate networks that have some kind of filtering or custom DNS service. We fixed it modifying etc/docker/daemon.json following this guide: [https://development.robinwinslow.uk/2016/06/23/fix-docker-networking-dns/]

And *could not connect to server: Connection refused* error might be caused because the execution script that loads content of .*sql* files is executed too earlier. There is an sleep time (set by default to 2 seconds) that might not be enough on faster computers. Could you try increasing that factor? (line 123 of deploy_explorer.sh);;;

