 }
}
 
{code}
As you can see I define only 1 peer in configuration file but problem is in my dashboard peer value increments indefinitely as you can see in attachments below.

!be.png!

Am I doing something wrong here or  is this bug in blockchain explorer?

HL API with Node.js implementation working fine with same config settings which I use for Explorer (TLS Enabled). It was working with Explorer before recent changes.

I noticed that after the latest commits regarding the discovery service, my Explorer is failing to start when grabbing the genesis block for the default channel. This is because for some reason when it tries to load the default channel it tries to do so ALWAYS with discovery: true. But discovery on the default channel is returning an incorrect orderer url (grpcs://localhost:7050, which is not in ANY of my config files, a separate issue which i am still debugging).

FabricClient.js:

 
{code:java}
await this.defaultChannel.initialize(

  {
    discover: true,
    target: this.defaultPeer,
    asLocalhost: asLocalhost
  }

);
{code}
 

However, I *do not want this* because I have set the flag: *initialize-with-discovery to false*. My work around is that this code should not run if initialize-with-discovery is set to false:

 

 
{code:java}
if ("initialize-with-discovery" flag === 'true') {
  await this.defaultChannel.initialize(

    {
      discover: true,
      target: this.defaultPeer,
      asLocalhost: asLocalhost
    }

  );
  ...
  try {      // load default channel network details from discovery
    const result = await this.defaultChannel.getDiscoveryResults();
    } catch (e) {... }

} else {

  await this.defaultChannel.initialize(
    {
      discover: false,
      target: this.defaultPeer,
      asLocalhost: asLocalhost
    }

  );

  // Do NOT try to load discovery results

}
{code}
 

 

Has anyone else encountered this issue?

